claim.claim-text:
7. A method of capturing overlapping images, comprising:
capturing a first image when an optical axis is in a first position;
storing the first image;
displaying a part of the first image;
moving the optical axis from the first position;
stopping movement of the optical axis when the displayed part of the first image is overlapped with a corresponding portion of a second image such that a composite image can be subsequently generated from the first image and the second image; and
capturing the second image.

16. A device configured for capturing overlapping images, comprising:
an image capture device configured to capture a first image when an optical axis is in a first position;
a storage unit configured to store the first image;
a display monitor configured to displaying a part of the first image;
a unit configured to move the optical axis from the first position;
a unit configured to stop movement of the optical axis when the display part of the first image is overlapped with a corresponding portion of a second image such that a composite image can be subsequently generated from the first image and the second image; and
a capturing unit configured to capture the second image.
